My friend @weaksaucephilly took me to an amazing Lao restaurant recently and I can’t stop thinking about it. The flavors are so rich and original 🔥 You must check this place out for yourselves, I insist. Shoutout to @vientianebistro for the great time. 
- Roasted half duck w/ Sauté with garlic, bell peppers, broccoli, carrots and onions in a spicy sauce.
- Homemade Beef Jerky (Seen Haag) - Marinated beef with steam vegetables, served with chili peanut paste
- Minced pork Laab (2 pics) w/ marinated with roasted rice powder, lime juice, kalanga, lemongrass, mint, cilantro, beansprouts and served with sticky rice.
- Papaya salad (Thum-mak-hoong) - w/ Shredded papaya with tomatoes, garlic, chili, lime juice, and the optional fermented crab to make it Lao style
#phillyfoodporn ✌🏼

Finally tried the Ethiopian fried chicken from @dorobetphl - STRAIGHT CRACK 🔥 🍗 
- Tumeric Lemon (mild)
- Berbere (Ethiopian spice mix) (spicy) 
- Farro salad
100% worth the drive across the city for me. Oh, and it’s gluten free 😎 
Check them out! #phillyfoodporn

I got humbled at @eatpaesanos with these dishes that filled us up quick af. 😅 
- Meatball Bosciaola sandwich
- Paesano sandwich
- Arancini
- Gattifin (crispy fried spinach, potato, & mozzarella ravioli)
#phillyfoodporn

Farewell tour stop: New phone means portrait mode for my food 📸 🖼️ Started my 2023 off right with a Gritty sandwich from @mikesbbq_215: Smoked Brisket Cheesesteak w/ Cooper sharp whiz, fried onions, lettuce, tomato, gritty sauce, potato sticks, and optional fried egg 🔥 🔥 
#phillyfoodporn

I have to give a special shoutout to my boy @trinheatss and his crew for throwing an amazing private pop-up dinner last night. Everything this guy churns out is absolute fire and it’s great to see his career take off in the way it has in the last few years. It was lovely to sit in such a small, private setting with complete strangers who were as excited for the food as we were. Definitely give him a follow to keep up with what he’s doing 💪🏼 🍲 🔥 

The Spread:
- Smoked Maitake and strip steak w/ rauram, crispy rice, mushroom XO tare (with egg yolk)
- Lotus root salad w/ shrimp, head cheese, herbs, and shrimp crackers
- “Big Ol’ Pork Mochi Dumpling” w/ ginger, bone broth, and pork cracklin’
- Kombu Jime Crudo w/ winter flounder, snap peas, and lemon balm
- “Not” Texas Road House rolls w/ maple fish sauce butter
- Parisian egg tart w/ espresso créme
 
#phillyfoodporn

Madeira braised pork shank with candied sweet potatoes and simmered cabbage from @rexphl - Definitely worth your time, money, and undivided attention 😋 
#phillyfoodporn

I’m officially jumping on the seltzer hype train, and it’s because of the fantastic cocktails and dishes I had at @tworobbersfishtown - Which is marketed as a seltzer and burger joint, but has way much more than just that. There hasn’t been much of a reason for me to get into seltzers until I checked this spot out. Whether you’re coming with your carnivorous or vegetarian friends, there’s something for everyone on their menu. And I’m happy to report that it’s all fantastic.

- Scallop Crudo:
Raw scallops, buttermilk, housemade lemongrass kosho, marrow bean shoyu, chive oil.
- Grilled Avocados w/ ponzu, wasabi
- Eggplant Tonnato w/
tonnato sauce, salmon roe, ikura, mint (this was our favorite)
- The Burger
Double smash beef patty, pickles, onions,
American cheese, burger sauce, bun
- Pineapple Ginger Buck:
Bourbon, pineapple, ginger, lime, Two Robbers Pineapple Ginger.
- Raspberry Daisy:
Rum, raspberry, lime, Two Robbers Raspberry Lime
- Mango Punch Michelada
Mango, lime, Valentina, Tajin chili salt, Two Robbers Mango Punch (this was absolutely fire 🔥)
- Poutine w/
Fries, cheese curds, beef gravy

#phillyfoodporn #seltzer #fishtown #philly #phillyfood

Farewell tour stop: Been coming to @breakfast.at.sulimays since I first moved into the neighborhood and quickly became friends with then owner, @lucretia.sulimay, who we see as one of our favorite people and a cornerstone of the community. She doesn’t own or operate the space anymore as she has decided to focus her efforts to traveling across the world more than anyone else I know (although she is still very much affiliated with the restaurant). Still, I come in as often as I can to get my fix of the Fishtown scrapple, a dish that the current owner created when he took over.
Spicy whitefish “scrapple,” heirloom tomato, sunny side up eggs, pickled long hots & comeback sauce (contains dairy) served with roasted potatoes. One of my favorite breakfast platters ever. #phillyfoodporn ✌🏼

Finally got to sit down at @tabachoyphilly to try their Filipino delicacies. Happy to say that they are well worth the visit. 
- Ukoy - shrimp, carrot, sweet potato, and cilantro fritter, served w/ chili vinegar 
- Pork Sigsig - minced pork belly, peppers, onions, garlic, chili, citrus, fried egg, served w/ rice
- Chance’s fried chicken w/ house pork gravy and atchara 
- Mushroom Adobo w/ shiitake, soy, vinegar, kale, and grated daikon
- Ube Ice Cream- made with purple yams, puffed rice, caramel drizzle, and a fried banana spring roll
#phillyfoodporn

location.city_name: Five Saints Distilling and International Spirits, LLC

social_posts.post_text: A huge thanks to @fivesaintsdistilling for sending me these fine spirits to test out. I was sent a bottle of their rare Pennsylvania whiskey (a smooth and mild whiskey with very little bite), Maple bourbon butter pecan rum, Raspberry Lavender Absinthe Americane, and Blood Orange Liquer. All of which made for delicious cocktails created by yours truly. With the Pennsylvania whiskey, I made some summer cocktails with ginger beer and a splash of lemonade (which went down super easy). With the Maple Burboun Butter Pecan Rum, I made my own version of a White Russian (an ode to my favorite movie, The Big Lebowski) with some Kaluah, half & half cream, and garnished it with shaved coffee beans. With the Absinthe Americane, we made some Raspberry Lavender Absinthe frozen lemonade smoothies, which were fantastic for sipping on in the back yard during the heat this past weekend. I highly recommend checking them out or trying their spirits at the many bars they are available at in the area (I know for a fact that the whiskey is available at @cantina.la.martina.philly). Be sure to tag me if you end up making something with these! #phillyfoodporn #fivesaintsdistilling #fivesaintsdistillery #fivesaints

With all due respect to the other spots, I dare say that @cantina.la.martina.philly is the best Mexican restaurant in the city. I say this as a person of Mexican decent who thinks the selections of this quality in Philly are few and far between. Not only are their dishes original and delicious as all hell, but incredibly affordable for the amount of quality you get. For real though, when’s the last time you got Taco-Tuesday tacos for 2 bucks a piece of this quality? We got a pizza box crammed with nothing but straight fire for only $20, which was refreshing as hell to see, especially in today’s economy. 
The last time I posted pics of their food, it was on my old phone and, frankly, didn’t do their food justice. So check out the additional pics I added of their taco platter (not to be confused with their Taco-Tuesday selections) and their AMAZING Mixiote dish ~ Braised Goat in chile sauce topped with nopales salad, served in a corn husk.
Be sure to give them a follow and hop on over to their spot for some grub and one of their awesome special events held in their backyard area. #phillyfoodporn #philly #phillyfood #mexicanfood #phillymexicanfood

@somersetsplits makes the coolest sundaes that you should try. Check ‘em out: 
“The Spring Breakers Sundae” (I was late to grabbing this one while it was available, but they were kind enough to make it for me anyway)- Mango ice cream, Tajine spiced gummy bears, toasted marshmallow, and a hot cheeto 🔥 
“Sundae Driver” - Mint Chocolate chip ice cream, crushed Oreos, chocolate fudge, toasted marshmallow, whipped cream, and rainbow sprinkles upon our request. 
Their IG has way more of their weekly specials. I encourage you to check them out 😎 🍨 
#phillyfoodporn

I trekked down to the Northeast to check out @bkphilly267, an Indian food truck making traditional and not-so-traditional Indian dishes that were good as fuck. Like their chicken tikka cheesesteak, massala fries, chicken tenders, lamb biryani, and samosas. If you’re in the northeast and near the intersection of Cottman and Algon (at the Lukoil station right next to Northeast High School), I highly recommend checking them out (once the air clears up, of course) ✌🏼 #phillyfoodporn

Had an excellent overnight stay at @daddyolbi in Long Beach Island last night. A nice little boutique hotel with a solid restaurant that serves great locally sourced dishes. It had a sweet roof deck with a full bar, a swanky garden bar in the back, and it’s only a few steps away from the beach. They conveniently provide towels, beach chairs, and an umbrella so you don’t have to bring all that yourself. If you’re looking for a quick beach getaway in a chill spot with friendly service, check them out ✌🏼 🏖️ 
We had their Scallops with applewood bacon and sweet pea risotto, Lancaster Chicken Milanese, and a bunch of other delicious dishes that had us stuffed beyond all expectations. Check out all of their other good stuff I had in my stories! #phillyfoodporn
Pastrami, egg, and cheese sando and "Latka'd" hash brown with dill cream from @middlechildclubhouse  #phillyfoodporn

Yes, it’s soup season, but definitely don’t sleep on Szechuan season either. Not to talk down on our beloved soups, but there’s nothing quite as comforting on a cold, rainy day than some hot and spicy Chinese food to keep your blood flowing. I highly recommend checking out @emeirestaurant for just that. It’s been on the top of my list for Szechuan since it’s opened and it hasn’t let me down once. Pictured is their dry-fried spicy lamb slices seasoned with cumin, stir fried spicy pork cracklings w/ fresh long hot peppers, famous Sichuan Kung Pao Chicken, Sliced Pork Belly with Garlic, Chiles, and Soy Sauce, and Homemade Pork Dumplings in Hot Chili oil. This place is pure fire 🔥 🍚 🥢 ✌🏼 #phillyfoodporn

Ever have an Indian style taco or hot dog? 

I took another visit over to @bkphilly267, this great Indian food truck in the Northeast, to try their new specialty items and I gotta say that it’s worth the trek. With a more modern take on some of my favorite Indian dishes, this spot makes super casual plates that I feel anyone would enjoy, especially if they’re new to Indian cuisine and want to dip their toes into it. Their new specials, like the Naan Taco (1st pic), Tandoori Hot Dog (2nd and 3rd pic), Tandoori Steak Wrap (4th pic), Kebab Tikka Masala (5th and 6th pic), and the Mango Lassi (last pic) were all incredibly tasty takes on the more traditional dishes I’m used to when it comes to Indian food in this city. It’s a shame that this spot isn’t located closer to Center City because it would CLEAN UP at one of the late night corners with plenty of walk-up traffic. Regardless, I highly recommend visiting this spot if you’re looking for Indian styled street food with a great twist (or if you just want some of the classic dishes as well). Check them out at 7300 Algon Ave, parked right across from Northeast High School. I truly wish this spot nothing but success. #phillyfoodporn
